DexC2C.doResolveDispute (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#764-803) sends eth to arbitrary user
	Dangerous calls:
	- _buyer.transfer((_value - _totalFees) * _buyerPercent / 100) (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#787-789)
	- _seller.transfer((_value - _totalFees) * (100 - _buyerPercent) / 100) (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#790-793)

DexC2C.transferMinusFees (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#1029-1049) sends eth to arbitrary user
	Dangerous calls:
	- _to.transfer(_value - _totalFees) (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#1043-1045)
params in DexC2C.createEscrow (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#851) is a local variable never initialiazed

DexC2C.doResolveDispute (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#764-803) does not use the value returned by external calls:

	-escrowData.removeEscrow(escrow.tradeHash) (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#1022-1023)

Reentrancy in DexC2C.doResolveDispute (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#764-803):
	External calls:
	- _totalFees += getTokenAmount(_token,GAS_doResolveDispute * uint256(tx.gasprice)) (/unique_contracts/0xf2d48b82f2f90a0d589ea144579c6f8c5a10f652.sol#778-780)
	State variables written after the call(s):
